quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  17,67,"When you are touched with hardship at sea, you ňĻtotallyňļ forget all ňĻthe godsňļ you ňĻnormallyňļ invoke, except Him. But when He delivers you ňĻsafelyňļ to shore, you turn away. Humankind is ever ungrateful"
  17,68,"Do you feel secure that He will not cause the land to swallow you up, or unleash upon you a storm of stones? Then you will find none to protect you"
  17,69,"Or do you feel secure that He will not send you back to sea once again, and send upon you a violent storm, drowning you for your denial? Then you will find none to avenge you against Us"
  17,70,"Indeed, We have dignified the children of Adam, carried them on land and sea, granted them good and lawful provisions, and privileged them far above many of Our creatures"
  17,71,ňĻBeware ofňļ the Day We will summon every people with their leader.¬†So whoever will be given their record in their right hand will read it ňĻhappilyňļ and will not be wronged ňĻeven by the width ofňļ the thread of a date stone
  17,72,"But whoever is blind ňĻto the truthňļ in this ňĻworldňļ will be blind in the Hereafter, and ňĻevenňļ far more astray from the ňĻRightňļ Way"
  17,73,"They definitely ňĻthought theyňļ were about to lure you away from what We have revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ, hoping that you would attribute something else to Us falsely‚ÄĒand then they would have certainly taken you as a close friend"
  17,74,"Had We not made you steadfast, you probably would have inclined to them a little"
  17,75,"and then We truly would have made you taste double ňĻpunishmentňļ both in this life and after death, and you would have found no helper against Us"
